[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026791&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026791&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

The domain system, as most of the people on this list probably already
know, provides several record types for handling "aliasing", "forward-
ing", and "mailing list" situations:  namely, MB, MR, MG, and MINFO.

Is anyone out there on the net currently using MB or MR records?

Has anyone modified either Sendmail or MMDF-II to look for MB or MR rec-
ords when delivering mail?

Similarly, has anyone adapted their mail system to use MG and MINFO rec-
ords for delivery to mailing lists?  (Please note that I am not neces-
sarily advocating the use of MG and MINFO; I realize that some may still
feel that it is better simply to send mailing-list submissions to the
host handling the list, rather than have the sending host expand the
list itself.)

